WEBVTT

01:40.509 --> 01:45.830
[Speed and Love]

01:46.300 --> 01:48.800
[Episode 12]

01:50.000 --> 01:53.530
Tuesday, I love you in Thai.

02:03.300 --> 02:05.820
Didn't you ask me yesterday about someone

02:05.870 --> 02:07.310
called Death?

02:07.380 --> 02:08.750
I know who he is.

02:18.980 --> 02:22.010
Yesterday, I was playing basketball
in the neighborhood,

02:22.010 --> 02:23.240
and some guys happened to

02:23.240 --> 02:24.430
mention him.

02:24.510 --> 02:27.200
So, I specifically asked them about him.

02:27.900 --> 02:30.020
They said that Death was

02:30.079 --> 02:31.740
a senior from a previous year.

02:31.920 --> 02:33.660
He was into racing,
had his own racing team,

02:33.660 --> 02:35.450
and often participated in
illegal street races.

02:35.450 --> 02:38.100
The reason he's called "Death"

02:38.160 --> 02:40.280
is because he was so fast

02:40.410 --> 02:42.480
that anyone who raced him was doomed—

02:42.500 --> 02:44.980
they lost before they even reached
the final lap.

02:44.980 --> 02:45.829
Too bad

02:46.180 --> 02:48.820
his car was confiscated later,

02:48.870 --> 02:49.930
so he quieted down.

02:50.430 --> 02:52.290
After that, no one knows what happened—

02:52.290 --> 02:53.760
Death suddenly

02:53.790 --> 02:56.320
disappeared a month or two
before the college entrance exam

02:56.320 --> 02:57.980
and never came back to school.

02:58.140 --> 02:59.360
Shame, though—

02:59.540 --> 03:01.820
he had pretty good grades.

03:01.920 --> 03:03.320
Quite legendary, right?

03:08.170 --> 03:10.230
Why were you asking about him anyway?

03:15.290 --> 03:16.320
Class begins!

03:20.400 --> 03:22.710
Today, we're going to learn
the local dialect.

03:22.710 --> 03:24.310
The words we're learning are

03:24.660 --> 03:25.630
"desert,"

03:26.350 --> 03:27.460
"autumn,"

03:27.850 --> 03:29.180
and "transportation."

03:53.250 --> 03:55.010
I've forgotten how to get home.

03:56.530 --> 03:59.280
[Take bus No. 8.]

03:57.410 --> 03:58.210
Take bus No. 8.

04:01.340 --> 04:02.320
How many stops?

04:03.800 --> 04:04.530
Three stops.

04:06.230 --> 04:07.290
What are you doing?

04:08.650 --> 04:09.370
Busy.

04:10.060 --> 04:11.300
[Busy.]

04:28.660 --> 04:29.520
Whatcha doing?

04:31.600 --> 04:32.800
You're peeking at me.

04:33.470 --> 04:34.240
No.

04:34.260 --> 04:36.320
I just want to know what you're doing.

04:39.770 --> 04:41.630
Fine, fine, I'll leave you alone.

04:45.680 --> 04:49.600
[Professional Oversleeper]

05:07.540 --> 05:09.310
Mu, what are your plans after school?

05:09.310 --> 05:10.370
Let's go together!

05:10.400 --> 05:12.950
It's not safe for you to be alone.
I'll walk you.

05:12.950 --> 05:13.830
Let's go together.

05:13.830 --> 05:15.370
-Let go.
-Let go of her!

05:31.550 --> 05:32.700
Why are you here?

05:34.370 --> 05:35.300
Just passing by.

05:37.659 --> 05:39.590
Who... Who is he?

05:40.210 --> 05:41.159
Death.

05:46.659 --> 05:47.460
Let's go home.

06:06.080 --> 06:06.990
Awesome!

06:07.030 --> 06:08.410
Our first performance went so well!

06:08.410 --> 06:10.420
We can make the donation next week.

06:11.560 --> 06:13.740
-I told you so!
-Great!

06:13.820 --> 06:15.120
Keep these safe.

06:17.180 --> 06:19.200
Mu, you really know how to pick songs.

06:19.200 --> 06:20.650
The song "The Moon Represents My Heart"

06:20.650 --> 06:21.830
is really catchy.

06:21.950 --> 06:23.040
I told you so.

06:29.730 --> 06:30.320
I...

06:30.800 --> 06:32.460
Didn't I tell you last time...

06:36.450 --> 06:37.240
A chat?

06:39.950 --> 06:41.310
You're not here for me?

06:44.650 --> 06:46.950
That man you've been pining for...

06:48.090 --> 06:50.490
It wouldn't happen to be
Jin Zhao, would it?

06:52.460 --> 06:53.330
So?

06:53.770 --> 06:54.800
Are you in or not?

07:04.920 --> 07:06.850
The woman Jin Zhao has his eye on...

07:07.640 --> 07:08.840
is a coward?

07:19.780 --> 07:20.710
I'll go with you.

07:23.320 --> 07:24.780
The car is at the entrance.

07:25.620 --> 07:26.200
Mu,

07:26.230 --> 07:28.130
you can't go. You fell for her trick.

07:28.130 --> 07:29.400
She was just goading you.

07:29.400 --> 07:31.810
I'll take you out
through the back door later...

07:31.810 --> 07:32.700
Don't tell him.

07:36.409 --> 07:37.090
Mu...

07:45.270 --> 07:46.640
Sit wherever you want.

08:08.990 --> 08:09.940
Are you okay?

08:10.680 --> 08:11.360
I'm fine.

08:11.790 --> 08:13.050
I'm not that delicate.

08:17.760 --> 08:18.710
To be honest,

08:18.730 --> 08:20.160
before meeting you, I never knew Jin Zhao

08:20.160 --> 08:21.490
was into girls like you.

08:25.950 --> 08:28.070
You've known Jin Zhao for a long time?

08:29.550 --> 08:31.190
When he first started working
at Wan's Garage,

08:31.190 --> 08:32.650
I heard people talking about

08:32.650 --> 08:34.510
a handsome new guy who had joined—

08:34.659 --> 08:37.190
not only efficient
but also very capable too.

08:37.820 --> 08:38.940
The first time I met him

08:38.940 --> 08:40.669
was at the garage's repair bay.

08:44.970 --> 08:47.370
[WJAUTO]

08:45.630 --> 08:48.090
That night, while driving back
from the bar,

08:48.400 --> 08:49.970
I passed the garage

08:50.870 --> 08:52.870
and saw the lights still on so late.

08:53.510 --> 08:55.310
So, I pulled over to check it out.

08:57.270 --> 08:59.100
I'd never seen an apprentice

08:59.120 --> 09:00.810
as focused as he was.

09:38.650 --> 09:40.180
What's wrong with this car?

09:40.210 --> 09:41.290
The valve is loose.

09:41.440 --> 09:42.970
Just needs to be tightened.

09:45.330 --> 09:46.680
What's your name?

09:49.440 --> 09:50.250
Jin Zhao.

09:53.780 --> 09:54.680
I'm Wan Qing.

10:01.150 --> 10:02.080
Nice to meet you.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.850
Do you believe in love at first sight?

10:21.520 --> 10:24.250
Maybe it was when he lifted his head
that I noticed

10:24.290 --> 10:26.830
he not only had a great build
but also a handsome face.

10:26.830 --> 10:28.560
That was when I became interested in him.

10:28.560 --> 10:29.870
Sometimes, when I was out late,

10:29.870 --> 10:31.780
I'd specifically swing by the garage

10:31.780 --> 10:33.040
to have a smoke with him

10:33.450 --> 10:34.790
or just do nothing—

10:34.810 --> 10:36.390
sitting beside him, playing games,

10:36.390 --> 10:38.590
or keeping him company while he worked.

10:40.230 --> 10:41.220
Honestly,

10:41.410 --> 10:43.290
there were tons of mechanics his age

10:43.290 --> 10:44.800
working for my dad.

10:45.420 --> 10:46.420
They came and went

10:46.560 --> 10:48.210
like a revolving door.

10:48.440 --> 10:49.700
Few of them stayed put.

10:49.860 --> 10:52.390
They only worked
as much as they were paid for.

10:52.440 --> 10:53.640
But he was different.

10:54.220 --> 10:55.390
He was the only guy I'd ever seen

10:55.390 --> 10:56.950
who always had a book in his hand.

10:56.950 --> 10:59.560
Others kept their lockers
full of cigarettes and alcohol,

10:59.560 --> 11:00.960
but his was full of books.

11:01.520 --> 11:02.820
He'd already filled

11:02.920 --> 11:04.650
more than two large notebooks.

11:05.660 --> 11:07.660
And his handwriting was beautiful.

11:13.850 --> 11:15.690
Come on, coffee for everyone!

11:15.800 --> 11:17.240
Stop working. Take a break.

11:17.240 --> 11:18.770
What brings you here today?

11:18.790 --> 11:21.590
This is my dad's garage.
I can come whenever I want.

11:23.370 --> 11:24.300
Come on, come on.

11:24.570 --> 11:25.340
Coffee, here you go.

11:25.340 --> 11:26.070
Jin Zhao.

11:26.600 --> 11:28.330
I heard you don't like sweet stuff.

11:28.330 --> 11:29.530
This one has no sugar.

11:31.000 --> 11:31.760
Thanks.

11:49.090 --> 11:51.020
Your handwriting is so beautiful.

11:51.960 --> 11:53.320
Mine is terrible.

11:54.140 --> 11:55.740
Could you teach me sometime?

12:00.480 --> 12:01.480
I don't have time.

12:22.730 --> 12:24.810
Later, I heard from Crazy Jin

12:25.260 --> 12:27.690
that Jin Zhao had a little sister at home.

12:27.950 --> 12:29.410
She had congenital heart disease

12:29.410 --> 12:31.070
and needed surgery urgently.

12:32.140 --> 12:33.490
But his family

12:33.570 --> 12:35.900
couldn't afford such expensive surgery.

12:36.060 --> 12:37.570
It was Jin Zhao

12:37.570 --> 12:39.830
who scraped together the money himself.

12:40.720 --> 12:43.080
At that time, many mechanics at the garage

12:43.300 --> 12:45.020
would privately contact car owners

12:45.020 --> 12:47.450
to buy cheap used cars,

12:47.970 --> 12:50.300
fix them up, and resell them.

12:50.850 --> 12:53.190
They could make 10,000 to 20,000 yuan
on one flip,

12:53.190 --> 12:55.110
sometimes even more.

12:55.550 --> 12:58.210
Jin Zhao saw this as an opportunity
to make money

12:58.330 --> 13:00.180
and borrowed some money from Crazy Jin.

13:00.180 --> 13:02.420
He then bought a cheap car.

13:02.850 --> 13:04.450
A buyer told him that

13:04.690 --> 13:06.860
if he could boost
the car's 0-100 km/h acceleration

13:06.860 --> 13:08.660
and other performance aspects,

13:09.450 --> 13:10.530
he would pay more.

13:12.360 --> 13:14.620
Jin Zhao started researching on his own.

13:15.180 --> 13:17.110
He drew diagrams, modified parts,

13:17.330 --> 13:19.260
and pulled several all-nighters.

13:20.330 --> 13:22.610
He upgraded... what's it called...

13:22.680 --> 13:23.970
the transmission system

13:23.970 --> 13:25.100
and the powertrain.

13:29.150 --> 13:30.690
The buyer was very satisfied

13:30.690 --> 13:32.140
and paid him a large sum.

13:32.720 --> 13:34.480
Jin Zhao used this money

13:34.940 --> 13:36.740
to pay for his sister's surgery.

13:37.180 --> 13:38.300
Here, count it.

13:41.260 --> 13:42.390
Then what happened?

13:42.690 --> 13:43.780
Then...

13:44.780 --> 13:47.040
Jin Zhao told Crazy Jin he wanted to quit;

13:47.260 --> 13:47.990
he was done.

13:48.300 --> 13:50.260
The college entrance exam was
coming up then.

13:50.260 --> 13:52.520
He probably wanted to focus on studying.

13:52.970 --> 13:54.930
I heard his grades were really good,

13:54.930 --> 13:56.860
though I don't know if that's true.

14:05.940 --> 14:06.970
It's true.

14:10.230 --> 14:11.360
Since childhood...

14:12.970 --> 14:14.300
he was always by my side.

14:15.000 --> 14:16.260
When we were little...

14:17.990 --> 14:19.660
he was always my role model.

14:20.730 --> 14:22.660
He could build very complex devices

14:22.660 --> 14:25.090
on his own when he was in his early teens.

14:26.770 --> 14:27.530
Really.

14:28.200 --> 14:31.000
I've seen him excel in so many ways.

14:33.260 --> 14:34.470
Back then, he

14:34.690 --> 14:35.890
wasn't like he is now.

14:36.470 --> 14:38.220
He had a bit of a scholarly air about him,

14:38.220 --> 14:39.380
quite attractive.

14:40.290 --> 14:42.090
When he said he quit, he meant it.

14:42.430 --> 14:44.200
I even cried over it once.

14:44.440 --> 14:46.300
I thought I'd never see him again.

14:49.870 --> 14:50.990
Jin Zhao...

14:53.180 --> 14:55.380
didn't take the college entrance exam.

14:56.610 --> 14:57.410
That's right.

14:57.940 --> 14:59.140
Did

15:00.020 --> 15:01.570
something happen to him?

15:07.460 --> 15:09.320
Something happened with the car.

15:11.450 --> 15:13.180
While the owner was driving,

15:13.780 --> 15:14.920
the car lost control.

15:14.920 --> 15:15.890
He survived

15:16.780 --> 15:17.850
but lost one leg.

15:18.950 --> 15:21.210
The subsequent investigation determined

15:21.210 --> 15:24.130
that the car lost control
due to illegal modifications.

15:24.130 --> 15:25.380
As the investigation progressed,

15:25.380 --> 15:26.940
it led to Jin Zhao.

15:27.420 --> 15:28.900
The victim's family believed

15:28.900 --> 15:30.810
that his aftermarket modifications
and sales

15:30.810 --> 15:32.140
created safety hazards

15:32.340 --> 15:33.890
that led to this negligent accident.

15:33.890 --> 15:35.140
They wanted to sue him.

15:35.140 --> 15:36.810
Crazy Jin was desperate at that time.

15:36.810 --> 15:38.980
He borrowed money from everyone

15:39.330 --> 15:40.710
to pay compensation

15:40.730 --> 15:42.900
and begged them not to sue Jin Zhao.

15:42.970 --> 15:44.210
If Jin Zhao had a criminal record,

15:44.210 --> 15:45.570
his life would be ruined.

15:45.570 --> 15:47.090
I was worried too.

15:47.160 --> 15:49.490
I quickly sold my newly bought sports car

15:49.620 --> 15:51.210
and gave all the money to Crazy Jin,

15:51.210 --> 15:52.780
hoping to help somehow.

15:57.330 --> 15:58.250
But...

15:59.850 --> 16:01.780
Jin Zhao told Crazy Jin

16:02.020 --> 16:03.620
he wouldn't accept my money.

16:08.420 --> 16:10.220
Maybe he didn't think much of me.

16:12.940 --> 16:14.670
Jin Zhao said he didn't want it.

16:15.520 --> 16:16.710
Did you tell him

16:16.730 --> 16:18.060
this money came from selling my car

16:18.060 --> 16:19.190
and had nothing to do with my dad?

16:19.190 --> 16:20.260
I told him everything.

16:20.260 --> 16:22.120
He said, "Thanks, but no thanks."

16:22.120 --> 16:24.520
Take it back quickly.
I've got things to do.

16:26.450 --> 16:27.980
Take it back quickly, Miss.

16:27.990 --> 16:29.520
I've got to get back to work.

16:42.890 --> 16:44.020
What happened next?

16:44.180 --> 16:45.610
Later, one of Jin Zhao's friends—

16:45.610 --> 16:47.670
a guy named Sanlai who usually seemed

16:48.020 --> 16:49.080
quite unreliable—

16:49.550 --> 16:51.790
sold off his fast-food restaurant,

16:52.020 --> 16:53.330
and they finally raised enough money.

16:53.330 --> 16:55.590
Only then did the victim agree to settle.

16:56.810 --> 16:58.380
After that incident...

16:59.630 --> 17:01.090
he didn't go back to school

17:01.450 --> 17:03.050
but went back to Wan's Garage

17:03.180 --> 17:04.579
to work as an apprentice.

17:05.770 --> 17:08.829
He did the dirtiest
and most exhausting work every day,

17:09.040 --> 17:10.180
with no fixed start

17:10.180 --> 17:11.770
or end time,

17:12.210 --> 17:14.490
working nonstop like a machine.

17:15.250 --> 17:16.490
It was as if he was using this as a way

17:16.490 --> 17:18.420
to punish himself for his mistake.

17:36.920 --> 17:37.560
Zhang,

17:37.730 --> 17:39.590
the car is fixed. Please check it.

17:46.020 --> 17:48.280
But later, as he gained more experience,

17:49.620 --> 17:51.140
my dad valued him highly

17:51.790 --> 17:53.720
and put him in charge of the garage.

17:54.470 --> 17:56.190
That was when he discovered

17:57.250 --> 17:59.010
that those old-timers were

17:59.140 --> 18:00.740
hoarding tons of used parts.

18:00.860 --> 18:02.140
Some of the bolder ones

18:02.210 --> 18:03.820
would swap out new parts

18:03.900 --> 18:05.210
for substandard parts

18:05.380 --> 18:07.090
or parts that car owners no longer wanted—

18:07.090 --> 18:08.530
taking the new parts from clients' cars

18:08.530 --> 18:09.820
and selling them.

18:10.730 --> 18:12.590
All just for some drinking money.

18:15.620 --> 18:16.590
Jin Zhao...

18:19.090 --> 18:21.050
He was framed, right?

18:23.680 --> 18:24.290
Yes.

18:25.070 --> 18:26.980
Someone tampered with the car.

18:29.860 --> 18:30.860
You know what?

18:32.000 --> 18:34.710
For a long time before delivery,

18:34.730 --> 18:36.590
that car was kept at Wan's Garage.

18:36.690 --> 18:38.420
But it wasn't the garage's car.

18:38.940 --> 18:39.770
It wasn't even

18:39.770 --> 18:41.500
a client's car from the garage.

18:41.900 --> 18:43.770
Even if it were a client's car,

18:43.960 --> 18:46.420
those people would have still
messed with it—

18:46.420 --> 18:48.100
let alone a car that Jin Zhao brought in

18:48.100 --> 18:50.630
with absolutely no connection
to the garage?

18:52.150 --> 18:53.260
That incident back then

18:53.260 --> 18:54.380
was Wan Dayong's fault.

18:54.380 --> 18:56.350
He tampered with the car's sensors

18:56.540 --> 18:58.000
and actuator components.

18:58.340 --> 19:00.470
Mr. Wan approached all of us privately

19:00.730 --> 19:02.140
and told us not to say a word about it.

19:02.140 --> 19:03.210
He asked us to keep

19:03.370 --> 19:04.610
this matter buried.

19:05.250 --> 19:06.530
Sacrificing him

19:06.770 --> 19:09.370
was the only way
to save the garage's business.

19:10.180 --> 19:11.430
That poor kid took the blame

19:11.430 --> 19:13.100
and even believed it was his own fault.

19:13.100 --> 19:14.690
We had no choice back then.

19:14.980 --> 19:16.460
We all needed to make money for our families

19:16.460 --> 19:17.790
and couldn't afford to lose our jobs.

19:17.790 --> 19:19.120
You understand, right?

19:27.330 --> 19:28.440
After that day,

19:28.780 --> 19:32.090
Jin Zhao left Wan's Garage,
where he had worked for three years,

19:32.090 --> 19:33.220
and never came back.

19:34.100 --> 19:35.560
When it comes down to it...

19:37.950 --> 19:40.010
it was Wan's Garage that wronged him.

19:43.860 --> 19:45.620
So Jin Zhao endured

19:45.620 --> 19:47.080
all this injustice alone,

19:48.080 --> 19:50.210
and I knew nothing about it.

19:51.450 --> 19:52.690
It's all my fault.

19:54.730 --> 19:56.770
I wasn't there for him.

19:58.550 --> 20:01.650
♪ I leave after your curtain call ♪

20:04.360 --> 20:07.550
♪ I ask the tired bird ♪

20:08.340 --> 20:11.400
♪ About your news ♪

20:13.660 --> 20:17.310
♪ You're too serious in
both your passion and silence ♪

20:19.630 --> 20:24.810
♪ That's why you're always
covered in scars ♪

20:26.460 --> 20:30.060
♪ If darkness can stop the pain ♪

20:30.370 --> 20:35.560
♪ I'll let you sleep a bit longer ♪

20:36.050 --> 20:36.690
Jiang Mu.

20:37.050 --> 20:41.060
♪ I'll stay by your side tonight ♪

20:41.840 --> 20:42.520
Jiang Mu?

20:43.940 --> 20:49.060
♪ I want to meet the dusk with you ♪

20:48.440 --> 20:49.110
Mu?

20:49.420 --> 20:53.300
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

20:50.710 --> 20:51.710
Zhao.

20:54.080 --> 21:00.120
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

20:57.290 --> 20:58.450
What were you thinking?

20:58.450 --> 21:00.310
Why did you drink so much with her?

21:00.420 --> 21:02.380
I wanted to drink myself.

21:00.570 --> 21:04.220
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

21:02.450 --> 21:03.100
Yeah.

21:03.490 --> 21:06.900
We girls are just having
a heart-to-heart chat.

21:04.700 --> 21:08.810
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

21:07.050 --> 21:08.380
What's wrong with that?

21:08.580 --> 21:09.860
Is it any of your business?

21:09.150 --> 21:13.310
♪ But I'm still waiting
for every dawn and dusk ♪

21:10.900 --> 21:12.960
Don't you know how much you can drink?

21:13.050 --> 21:14.620
Drink what?

21:13.340 --> 21:17.270
♪ To run towards you again ♪

21:17.300 --> 21:24.810
♪ Even if I hug you for a moment ♪

21:18.900 --> 21:20.380
Don't scold her.

21:21.730 --> 21:23.050
Scold me instead!

21:24.580 --> 21:25.660
It was my father!

21:26.250 --> 21:27.530
It was Wan's Garage!

21:28.050 --> 21:28.970
It was me!

21:29.560 --> 21:31.000
We've wronged you!

21:32.350 --> 21:34.340
I'll make it up to you on their behalf.

21:34.340 --> 21:35.470
Go ahead, yell at me.

21:37.540 --> 21:38.740
Yell at me.

21:40.880 --> 21:45.610
♪ Perhaps the tides have carried
all the echoes away ♪

21:42.960 --> 21:44.020
Can you still walk?

21:45.640 --> 21:46.680
No.

21:47.370 --> 21:52.760
♪ How could you not hear me at all? ♪

21:52.580 --> 21:53.580
Zhao.

21:53.800 --> 21:57.810
♪ Every time I see you ♪

21:57.910 --> 21:59.150
I'm back.

21:57.980 --> 22:02.680
♪ You take a part of my soul ♪

22:01.010 --> 22:03.100
I'll never leave you again.

22:04.470 --> 22:08.430
♪ And longing slips in ♪

22:04.970 --> 22:05.900
What did you say?

22:06.580 --> 22:07.770
I said...

22:08.680 --> 22:12.920
♪ I want to meet the dusk with you ♪

22:10.580 --> 22:13.050
Let's never be apart again, okay?

22:12.990 --> 22:16.760
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

22:17.400 --> 22:22.480
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

22:24.110 --> 22:27.750
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

22:27.860 --> 22:32.250
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

22:32.320 --> 22:34.320
♪ But I'm still waiting ♪

22:34.600 --> 22:36.250
♪ For every dawn and dusk ♪

22:36.270 --> 22:40.200
♪ To run towards you again ♪

22:40.580 --> 22:44.250
♪ Until I can embrace you ♪

22:46.620 --> 22:49.910
♪ For a lifetime ♪

22:52.420 --> 22:53.180
Qing.

22:53.510 --> 22:54.910
Why did you drink so much?

22:55.580 --> 22:56.510
Are you okay?

23:01.720 --> 23:02.650
Are you alright?

23:07.420 --> 23:08.500
He Zhang!

23:09.460 --> 23:11.310
Good timing. Sit.

23:11.490 --> 23:13.340
Have a few more drinks with me.

23:13.660 --> 23:14.940
Come on, sit.

23:16.680 --> 23:17.880
I'll get you a bottle.

23:18.730 --> 23:20.140
This bottle...

23:20.450 --> 23:21.530
Here you go.

23:22.940 --> 23:24.620
I'll have this one.

23:24.730 --> 23:25.530
Alright, stop drinking.

23:25.530 --> 23:26.580
You've had too much.

23:26.580 --> 23:31.100
Give it back to me! I want to drink!
I want to drink!

23:32.520 --> 23:34.520
Let me open it for you.

23:36.030 --> 23:37.490
Fine, I'll drink with you.

23:43.660 --> 23:45.350
Then let's toast.

23:45.830 --> 23:47.150
Cheers!

23:59.650 --> 24:02.250
[Speeding Auto House]

24:31.710 --> 24:33.660
Here. Have some honey water.

24:52.660 --> 24:53.590
Feeling better?

25:03.260 --> 25:04.780
What happened to your leg?

25:08.380 --> 25:09.210
Who did this?

25:09.610 --> 25:10.400
Wan Qing?

25:11.090 --> 25:12.570
It wasn't her.

25:16.690 --> 25:19.290
I accidentally
bumped into something myself.

25:28.920 --> 25:30.640
Do you like her?

25:38.070 --> 25:38.790
Who?

25:42.380 --> 25:43.250
Wan Qing.

25:44.140 --> 25:45.300
I don't care.

25:47.290 --> 25:49.290
No matter how nice she's been to you,

25:49.440 --> 25:51.720
you can't like her.

26:01.100 --> 26:02.300
Have you sobered up?

26:03.420 --> 26:05.020
Saying stuff like that to me.

26:14.410 --> 26:15.470
It's getting late.

26:17.230 --> 26:18.430
Let me help you to bed.

26:33.070 --> 26:33.900
I...

26:36.770 --> 26:38.430
I'm all grown up now.

27:08.000 --> 27:09.000
Jiang Mu, you...

27:14.310 --> 27:15.390
When did you...

27:48.280 --> 27:50.780
Why are you out here
in the middle of the night, moon-gazing?

27:50.780 --> 27:53.180
Are you crazy?
You scared the hell out of me!

27:59.170 --> 28:00.430
Someone was just here?

28:01.690 --> 28:02.340
Yeah.

28:02.640 --> 28:04.150
Just finished chatting with them.

28:04.150 --> 28:04.760
Who?

28:05.940 --> 28:07.670
Your little fangirl, Wan Qing.

28:10.110 --> 28:11.180
Wasn't she drunk?

28:11.820 --> 28:12.450
Yeah.

28:12.770 --> 28:15.290
She was wasted and forced He Zhang

28:15.290 --> 28:16.330
to bring her over here.

28:16.330 --> 28:18.010
She even tried to break into your garage.

28:18.010 --> 28:20.050
I just saw you
carrying Jiang Mu back inside,

28:20.050 --> 28:22.100
so I couldn't let her
ruin your moment, right?

28:22.100 --> 28:23.690
Well, lucky you.

28:24.140 --> 28:26.020
She grabbed me, crying and making a scene.

28:26.020 --> 28:28.350
She told me all about her feelings
for you—

28:28.500 --> 28:29.500
her secret crush,

28:29.530 --> 28:30.510
obvious affection,

28:30.510 --> 28:31.910
and her unrequited love.

28:32.300 --> 28:34.560
She went through the whole story with me.

28:39.030 --> 28:39.660
Oh, right.

28:42.120 --> 28:43.520
Wan Qing just told me that

28:43.580 --> 28:45.250
when they were drinking, she told Jiang Mu

28:45.250 --> 28:46.340
all about the old grudges

28:46.340 --> 28:48.000
between you and Wan's Garage.

28:49.250 --> 28:50.980
Jiang Mu wasn't upset, was she?

28:52.100 --> 28:53.290
Zhao.

28:55.340 --> 28:56.530
I'm back.

28:58.460 --> 29:00.450
I'll never leave you again.

29:07.120 --> 29:07.810
No.

29:29.950 --> 29:30.760
Brandy.

29:34.300 --> 29:36.500
Jiang Mu is actually a pretty nice girl.

29:38.600 --> 29:39.760
Look at her—

29:40.490 --> 29:41.540
she's tall,

29:41.860 --> 29:43.010
fair-skinned,

29:43.750 --> 29:45.550
with long, straight black hair.

29:45.800 --> 29:47.600
And she has a great personality.

29:48.100 --> 29:50.530
Sure, she can be
a little dramatic sometimes,

29:50.530 --> 29:52.090
but she's smart

29:52.580 --> 29:53.820
and quick to learn.

29:55.140 --> 29:56.380
Her only flaw is

29:56.630 --> 29:58.030
that she's a picky eater.

29:58.820 --> 30:00.210
But being picky means
she won't gain weight,

30:00.210 --> 30:01.270
so that's good too.

30:02.640 --> 30:03.480
You know what?

30:03.880 --> 30:05.880
Just imagine if Jiang Mu got chubby—

30:06.590 --> 30:07.940
all plump and fair,

30:09.100 --> 30:10.420
with two ponytails—

30:11.770 --> 30:13.180
she'd be so adorable.

30:16.290 --> 30:17.950
Did she pay you to say all that?

30:18.080 --> 30:19.880
Why are you praising her so much?

30:20.030 --> 30:21.050
What are you talking about?

30:21.050 --> 30:22.660
I'm just telling the truth.

30:27.140 --> 30:29.470
Or do you think I'm wrong about something?

30:31.870 --> 30:32.870
No. It's all true.

30:37.030 --> 30:38.360
What do you think of her?

30:39.220 --> 30:39.980
Pretty good.

30:42.890 --> 30:44.620
What about as your girlfriend?

30:48.550 --> 30:50.280
I've never thought about that.

30:53.350 --> 30:54.750
Well, think about it now.

30:57.790 --> 30:59.650
Why should I think about that now?

30:59.690 --> 31:00.860
You're not doing anything anyway.

31:00.860 --> 31:02.320
Just give it some thought.

31:06.710 --> 31:07.840
But I really...

31:08.390 --> 31:10.320
I really shouldn't think about it.

31:24.380 --> 31:25.650
Brandy, oh, Brandy.

31:28.010 --> 31:29.010
In this lifetime,

31:29.660 --> 31:31.860
if any girl ever gets into your heart...

31:34.890 --> 31:35.890
that girl...

31:39.970 --> 31:41.100
can only be Jiang Mu.

32:00.220 --> 32:02.020
She doesn't need to try to get in.

32:02.980 --> 32:04.380
She's always been there.

32:33.560 --> 32:34.430
What's wrong?

32:35.350 --> 32:36.750
Why did you drink so much?

32:40.250 --> 32:41.860
Because...

32:46.770 --> 32:49.920
I like you.

32:50.570 --> 32:52.850
I like you.

32:55.440 --> 32:57.330
I like you.

32:59.300 --> 33:01.260
I really like you.

33:02.940 --> 33:05.380
I've liked you for so long.

33:06.210 --> 33:09.040
Why don't you like me back?

33:12.040 --> 33:12.630
Act...

33:13.310 --> 33:14.040
Actually...

33:14.210 --> 33:15.180
-Actually, I…
-Really.

33:15.180 --> 33:17.730
I like you, Jin Zhao.

33:22.400 --> 33:24.010
I like you.

33:26.940 --> 33:28.310
I like you.

34:05.000 --> 34:06.490
Jin Zhao said he didn't want it.

34:06.490 --> 34:07.940
Take it back quickly, Miss.

34:07.940 --> 34:09.469
I've got to get back to work.

34:33.960 --> 34:34.860
This year, we won't put as much

34:34.860 --> 34:36.719
in the red envelopes for the kids.

34:39.770 --> 34:40.570
Put that down.

34:43.560 --> 34:44.400
Put it down.

34:47.940 --> 34:50.190
You dare covet this? Are you crazy?

34:52.219 --> 34:52.969
No drinking!

34:53.500 --> 34:55.030
You have to drive tomorrow!

34:55.739 --> 34:57.250
How can I sleep if I don't drink?

34:57.250 --> 34:59.200
And how can I drive if I don't sleep well?

34:59.200 --> 35:01.600
Anyway, you're not allowed to drink today!

35:01.760 --> 35:02.550
Put it back.

35:04.320 --> 35:06.520
Do I have to yell at you
for you to listen?

35:25.670 --> 35:28.730
Is it really appropriate for us
to just leave like this?

35:29.050 --> 35:30.490
Leaving Mu alone here?

35:31.450 --> 35:32.820
Why don't we take her with us?

35:32.820 --> 35:33.750
The whole family

35:34.050 --> 35:34.780
can enjoy a lively

35:34.780 --> 35:36.980
and cheerful New Year together.
Wouldn't that be nice?

35:36.980 --> 35:38.190
She won't go with us.

35:39.600 --> 35:41.730
Did you even ask her? What if she would?

35:43.570 --> 35:44.910
Zhao is busy at the garage.

35:44.910 --> 35:46.380
It's New Year,
and she'll be all alone here.

35:46.380 --> 35:47.420
How lonely that must be.

35:47.420 --> 35:49.020
If you don't believe me, let's make a bet.

35:49.020 --> 35:50.700
If I win, you'll let me drink...

35:50.700 --> 35:51.780
You... You...

35:52.530 --> 35:53.460
You asked for it.

35:54.010 --> 35:54.970
You idiot.

35:56.010 --> 35:58.470
Betting on our child?
You've really lost it.

35:58.850 --> 36:00.110
You've lost your mind.

36:02.870 --> 36:03.540
Anyway,

36:03.770 --> 36:04.690
no matter what,

36:05.450 --> 36:07.340
I'm giving Mu a big red envelope.

36:08.220 --> 36:10.080
She's spending the New Year here.

36:10.170 --> 36:12.370
We absolutely cannot treat her poorly.

36:12.890 --> 36:15.040
Normally, she'd be too shy to accept it.

36:15.040 --> 36:15.920
This is good.

36:16.630 --> 36:17.940
Whatever she wants to eat or drink,

36:17.940 --> 36:19.200
she can buy it herself.

36:24.720 --> 36:26.650
Why are you looking at me like that?

36:26.970 --> 36:27.660
Not enough?

36:28.180 --> 36:30.040
If it's not enough, I'll add more.

36:30.970 --> 36:35.740
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven...

36:38.010 --> 36:38.900
What?

36:39.030 --> 36:39.760
Juan,

36:40.500 --> 36:41.420
you're so kind.

36:46.340 --> 36:48.140
Took you long enough to realize.

36:49.140 --> 36:50.370
Is this enough or not?

36:51.170 --> 36:52.210
You decide.

36:56.420 --> 36:57.740
Then what will you decide?

36:57.740 --> 36:59.800
I'll follow your lead on everything.

37:02.520 --> 37:03.580
You're killing me.

37:17.020 --> 37:18.870
Are you done? Hurry up!

37:20.010 --> 37:21.420
Is this the last box?

37:21.850 --> 37:23.150
Stop talking so much.

37:23.170 --> 37:24.490
Take this down too.

37:29.170 --> 37:30.220
Mu,

37:30.510 --> 37:33.240
are you really not coming with us
for the New Year?

37:34.080 --> 37:36.080
Will you be okay staying here alone?

37:37.010 --> 37:39.340
I'm staying here to keep Jin Zhao company.

37:40.380 --> 37:41.630
You really do like him,

37:41.630 --> 37:43.490
always running over to his place.

37:45.250 --> 37:45.920
Here.

37:47.420 --> 37:49.080
Here's a red envelope for you.

37:49.700 --> 37:50.450
Thank you.

37:50.630 --> 37:52.160
Take good care of yourself.

37:52.200 --> 37:53.260
We'll be going now.

37:54.830 --> 37:55.540
Xin.

37:58.230 --> 37:59.890
Here's a red envelope for you.

38:00.530 --> 38:01.590
Thank you, Sister.

38:01.650 --> 38:02.530
Happy New Year.

38:02.650 --> 38:03.560
Happy New Year.

38:05.090 --> 38:05.820
We're going.

38:06.790 --> 38:07.850
We'll be back soon.

38:11.590 --> 38:12.150
Yes,

38:12.540 --> 38:13.830
I do like him.

38:33.130 --> 38:35.340
-Here it comes!
-Dark chocolate versus white chocolate!

38:35.340 --> 38:36.970
-Come on, everyone.
-Come on!

38:36.970 --> 38:38.700
-Let's toast!
-Cheers!

38:39.090 --> 38:39.950
Happy New Year!

38:39.970 --> 38:41.830
-Happy New Year!
-Happy New Year!

38:44.750 --> 38:46.550
Nothing beats an ice-cold beer.

38:50.510 --> 38:51.430
Sanlai!

38:53.630 --> 38:54.580
Jiang Mu?

38:56.860 --> 38:57.940
Happy New Year!

38:58.030 --> 38:58.960
Come on, come on!

38:59.090 --> 39:00.300
Why didn't you bring an umbrella
in this rain?

39:00.300 --> 39:01.590
What if you catch a cold?

39:01.590 --> 39:04.990
It's just drizzling.
Couldn't get a taxi during the New Year.

39:05.100 --> 39:07.030
Why didn't you ask me to pick you up?

39:07.170 --> 39:07.940
It's not far.

39:08.010 --> 39:09.410
I can come over by myself.

39:12.340 --> 39:13.260
Hurry, sit.

39:13.510 --> 39:14.800
-Is there any food left for me?
-Come on.

39:14.800 --> 39:16.000
Of course. Of course we do.

39:16.000 --> 39:17.750
Sanlai, get her something to eat.

39:17.750 --> 39:18.700
You think I need you to tell me that?

39:18.700 --> 39:20.490
I might go hungry,
but how could I let our Jiang Mu starve?

39:20.490 --> 39:20.970
I'll get you something to eat.

39:20.970 --> 39:21.890
Thanks, Sanlai.

39:21.890 --> 39:22.950
Don't catch a cold.

39:26.570 --> 39:28.030
Ji, you still wanna eat...

39:28.070 --> 39:28.680
I get it.

39:28.720 --> 39:29.900
I can take a hint. I'll sit here.

39:29.900 --> 39:31.310
I'll sit here. I'll sit here.

39:31.310 --> 39:32.380
Hurry, sit, sit.

39:35.190 --> 39:36.420
Come on. Let's chat.

39:36.940 --> 39:37.570
About that thing last time...

39:37.570 --> 39:40.370
Why aren't you spending the New Year
with your dad?

39:41.310 --> 39:42.300
Mrs. Zhao suddenly said

39:42.300 --> 39:44.860
she wanted to take Jin Xin back home
for a visit.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.130
Dad drove them there.

39:46.530 --> 39:48.380
They wanted me to come along too,

39:48.780 --> 39:49.900
but I wanted

39:50.270 --> 39:52.400
to stay and spend the New Year with you.

39:55.830 --> 39:57.430
Sis, here's your tableware!

39:58.370 --> 39:59.000
Eat some.

39:59.820 --> 40:00.530
Thank you.

40:04.390 --> 40:05.190
Come on, Crazy!

40:05.190 --> 40:05.650
Let's toast.

40:05.650 --> 40:06.420
-Happy New Year.
-Happy New Year.

40:06.420 --> 40:06.780
Cheers!

40:06.780 --> 40:08.040
Happy New Year, Crazy.

40:21.780 --> 40:22.510
Are you cold?

40:23.590 --> 40:24.590
My hands are cold.

40:52.860 --> 40:57.300
[Yearning Day and Night]
